    <briefdescription>
<para>1-D streaming signal detector with FFT-based correlation, integrate-and-dump, and configurable noise-referenced threshold. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Wraps a <ref refid="structcorr__state__t" kindref="compound">corr_state_t</ref> (FFT correlator + coherent int-dump) behind a double-mapped ring buffer so that arbitrary-length sample streams can be fed in any chunk size. After every int-dump a test statistic is computed:</para>
<para>test_stat = peak_mag / noise_est</para>
<para>where peak_mag = max|R&amp;#91;τ&amp;#93;| and noise_est is an aggregate (mean, median, min, or max) of |R&amp;#91;τ&amp;#93;| over a user-supplied bin range &amp;#91;noise_lo, noise_hi&amp;#93;. A detection event is emitted when test_stat &gt; threshold (or whenever threshold == 0.0, which means &quot;always fire&quot;).</para>
<para>The detector operates as a single-threaded object; do not call <ref refid="detector__core_8h_1a9f5e3f874de1cbb1fbebef891afbf49a" kindref="member">detector_push()</ref> concurrently from multiple threads.</para>
<para>Lifecycle: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keywordtype">float</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>complex<sp/>ref[N]<sp/>=<sp/>{<sp/>...<sp/>};</highlight></codeline>
